# Summary
This documentation explains how Amplitude defines and tracks user sessions, including session identification methods, timeout settings for mobile and web applications, and custom session property configurations. It details how session length is calculated, how to handle out-of-session events, and how to implement session tracking through SDKs or HTTP API.

